    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the author's intent in his original context. The movements below trace Psalm 140's argument through its four recognizable pericopes: the enemy's portrait (vv. 1-5), the confession of trust (vv. 6-7), the petition against enemy advancement (vv. 8-11), and the closing certainty (vv. 12-13). Where the Hebrew sharpens what the English can carry, a brief note follows.",
